rade Air]] | [[Osijek Airport|Osijek]] (suspended)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://avioradar.hr/index.php/hr/hrvatska/1951-trade-air-obustavio-letove-u-domacem-zracnom-prometu|title=Trade Air obustavio letove u doma\u0107em zra\u010dnom prometu}}</ref>\n<!-- -->\n| [[Tunisair]] | '''Seasonal charter:''' [[Monastir Habib Bourguiba International Airport|Monastir]] (begins 27 May 2020)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.routesonline.com/news/38/airlineroute/288883/tunisair-resumes-monastir-zagreb-charter-in-s20/ |title=Tunisair resumes Monastir \u2013 Zagreb charter in S20 |publisher=Routesonline |date=20 January 2020 |accessdate=20 January 2020}}</ref>\n<!-- -->\n| [[Turkish Airlines]] | [[Istanbul Airport|Istanbul]] (suspended)\n<!-- -->\n| [[Vueling]] | '''Seasonal:''' [[Barcelona\u2013El Prat Airport|Barcelona]]\n<!-- -->\n| [[Windrose Airlines]] | '''Seasonal:''' [[Kiev\u2013Boryspil]] (begins 2 June 2020)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://avioradar.hr/index.php/en/domestic-news-from-croatia/new-routes-announcement-of-new-routes/1847-zagreb-will-get-a-the-first-regular-route-from-ukraine |title=Zagreb will get a the[sic] first regular route from Ukraine |publisher=Avioradar |date= |accessdate=2020-01-30}}</ref>\n}}\n\n===Cargo===\n{{Airport-dest-list\n<!-- -->\n|[[DHL Aviation]] | [[Orio al Serio International Airport|Bergamo]], [[Bologna Guglielmo Marconi Airport|Bologna]], [[Cologne Bonn Airport|Cologne/Bonn]], [[Leipzig/Halle Airport|Leipzig]], [[Leo\u0161 Jan\u00e1\u010dek Airport Ostrava|Ostrava]], [[Venice Marco Polo Airport|Venice]]\n<!-- -->\n|[[MNG Airlines]] | [[Istanbul Atat\u00fcrk Airport|Istanbul\u2013Atat\u00fcrk]], [[Charles de Gaulle Airport|Paris\u2013Charles de Gaulle]]\n<!-- -->\n|[[Qatar Airways Cargo]] | [[Hamad International Airport|Doha]]\n<!-- -->\n}}\n\n==Ground transportation==\n\n===Public transportation===\nZAG can be reached from the city centre by scheduled local bus services (No.290) operated by [[Zagreba\u010dki elektri\u010dni tramvaj|ZET]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gettocenter.com/airport/ZAG-Zagreb-Airport|title=How to get from Zagreb Airport|publisher=|accessdate=15 March 2018}}</ref> or scheduled coach services operated by Croatia Airlines\u00b4 subsidiary Pleso Prijevoz.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://plesoprijevoz.hr/en/zagreb-croatia/|title=Pleso Prijevoz timetable|publisher=Pleso prijevoz|accessdate=22 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Statistics==\n===Traffic===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ Traffic at Zagreb Airport<ref name=\"zagreb-airport1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.zagreb-airport.hr/en/business/b2b/statistics/282|title= Statistics \u2013 Naslovna|publisher=MZLZ|accessdate=3 March 2019}}</ref>\n|- style=\"background:lightgrey;\"\n!width=\"80\"|Year\n! style=\"width:150px;\"|Passengers\n!width=\"50\"|Passenger % <br> Change\n! style=\"width:150px;\"|Aircraft Movements\n!width=\"50\"|Aircraft Movements% <br> Change\n! style=\"width:150px;\"|Cargo (tonnes)\n!width=\"50\"|Cargo % <br> Change\n|-\n|2000\n|1,149,830\n|n/a\n|n/a\n|n/a\n|7,388\n|n/a\n|-\n|2001\n|1,185,471\n|3.10{{increase}}\n|n/a\n|n/a\n|7,791\n|5.45{{increase}}\n|-\n|2002\n|1,203,436\n|1.52{{increase}}\n|n/a\n|n/a\n|7,347\n|5.70{{decrease}}\n|-\n|2003\n|1,314,652\n|9.24{{increase}}\n|n/a\n|n/a\n|8,608\n|17.16{{increase}}\n|-\n|2004\n|1,408,206\n|7.12{{increase}}\n|n/a\n|n/a\n|8,899\n|3.38{{increase}}\n|-\n|2005\n|1,551,519\n|10.18{{increase}}\n|37,484\n|n/a\n|12,492\n|40.38{{increase}}\n|-\n|2006\n|1,728,414\n|11.40{{increase}}\n|40,884\n|9.07{{increase}}\n|10,393\n|16.80{{decrease}}\n|-\n|2007\n|1,992,455\n|15.28{{increase}}\n|43,250\n|5.79{{increase}}\n|12,564\n|20.89{{increase}}\n|-\n|2008\n|2,192,453\n|10.04{{increase}}\n|44,542\n|2.99{{increase}}\n|12,697\n|1.06{{increase}}\n|-\n|2009\n|2,062,242\n|5.94 {{decrease}}\n|40,684\n|8.66{{decrease}}\n|10,065\n|20.73{{decrease}}\n|-\n|2010\n|2,071,561\n|0.45 {{increase}}\n|39,812\n|2.14{{decrease}}\n|8,156\n|18.97{{decrease}}\n|-\n|2011\n|2,319,098\n|11.95{{increase}}\n|42,360\n|6.40{{increase}}\n|